               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16870512-21-off99-c71" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870512-21-defend95 t16870512-21-off99 t16870512-21-verdict103"></join>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16870512-21-defend95" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Wood
                  <interp inst="t16870512-21-defend95" type="surname" value="Wood"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-21-defend95" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-21-defend95" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was tryed upon an Indictment of <rs id="t16870512-21-off99" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870512-21-off99" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-21-off99" type="offenceSubcategory" value="burglary"></interp>
               Burglary and Felony, for breaking the house of Sir 
                     
                        <persName id="t16870512-21-victim97" type="victimName">
                           John 
                           Roberts
                        <interp inst="t16870512-21-victim97" type="surname" value="Roberts"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16870512-21-victim97" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16870512-21-victim97" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870512-21-off99 t16870512-21-victim97"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , <rs id="t16870512-21-viclabel100" type="occupation">Barronet</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870512-21-victim97 t16870512-21-viclabel100"></join>, Scituate in <placeName id="t16870512-21-crimeloc101">Bromley by Bow</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-21-crimeloc101" type="placeName" value="Bromley by Bow"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870512-21-crimeloc101" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870512-21-off99 t16870512-21-crimeloc101"></join>, on the <rs id="t16870512-21-cd102" type="crimeDate">23d. of April</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870512-21-off99 t16870512-21-cd102"></join> last, and taking thence ten Peuter-Dishes, a Peuter Cestern, a Brass Pot, &amp;c.
            </rs> it was proved that the Goods mentioned, were found in an adjacent Pond, and those that found them, resolving to watch who would come to fetch them thence, the next Night they started out of the places where they were hid up-upon three Men, whom as they suppose by their Actions and discourse, came to get the the Peuter and Brass out of the Water, but two of them geting away, and he pleading they were in the Dark mistaken in the Man, he was <rs id="t16870512-21-verdict103" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870512-21-verdict103" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
